https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_uZYOgzYheU
last: 2:20:00

depency injection:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KMErAbXRQdg

mkdir MagicVilla && cd MagicVilla
dotnet new sln -n MagicVilla
dotnet new webapi -o MagicVilla_VillaAPI
dotnet sln MagicVilla.sln add MagicVilla_VillaAPI/MagicVilla_VillaAPI.csproj

cd MagicVilla_VillaAPI
dotnet add package Microsoft.AspNetCore.JsonPatch
dotnet add package Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.NewtonsoftJson

cd MagicVilla_VillaAPI
dotnet add package Serilog.AspNetCore

cd MagicVilla_VillaAPI
dotnet add package MySql.EntityFrameworkCore
dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore
dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Tools

cd MagicVilla_VillaAPI
dotnet tool install --global dotnet-ef
dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Design

https://www.infoworld.com/article/3691114/how-to-work-with-ef-core-migrations-in-aspnet-core.html
now instead using:
```
Add-Migration AddVillaTable
```

we can run:
```
dotnet ef migrations add AddVillaTable
dotnet ef migrations remove AddVillaTable

dotnet ef database update
```



Some errors:
microsoft.extensions.configuration.configurationextensions.getconnectionstring(...) returned null
This is coz db connection string returns null.
Solution: from(https://stackoverflow.com/questions/39628411/configuration-getconnectionstring-returns-null-when-running-asp-net-core-on-vs-c)
launch.json -> "cwd": "${workspaceFolder}/MagicVilla_VillaAPI",